                }
            ],
            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "upstream_solar_peak_5800K_500nm",
                    "description": "At default T = 5800 K (Sun's effective surface temperature) and λ = 500 nm (visible-green solar peak), Planck's law gives F_B_λ = 2π·c²·h·λ⁻⁵ / (exp(c·h/(k_B·λ·T)) - 1) = 84565887378394.64 W/m³ ≈ 8.46e13 W/m³ — the canonical solar-peak spectral irradiance per unit wavelength that anchors solar radiative transfer. The exponent c·h/(k_B·λ·T) = 1.986307254e-25 / 4.0049e-26 ≈ 4.9599 (dimensionless), so exp(4.9599) - 1 ≈ 141.59 dominates the Bose-Einstein occupation factor. Reproduces and tightens the upstream `Equation: BlackbodyRadiation (Eq. 4.2)` test (GasChem.jl test/radiation_fundamentals_test.jl:151-165) default case: upstream asserts F_B_λ ≈ 8.46e13 at rtol=5e-2, this one pins the exact IEEE-754 result 84565887378394.64 at rel=1e-9.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {},
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "F_B_λ", "time": 0.0, "expected": 84565887378394.64}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "upstream_earth_thermal_300K_10um",
                    "description": "At T = 300 K (~Earth surface temperature) and λ = 10 μm (thermal-IR peak), Planck's law gives F_B_λ = 31217606.963872723 W/m³ ≈ 3.12e7 W/m³ — the canonical longwave-outgoing-radiation peak that drives the planetary energy balance (S&P Eq. 4.6). The exponent c·h/(k_B·λ·T) ≈ 4.7949 here, just slightly below the solar-peak exponent of 4.96 — by Wien's displacement law, the peak shifts to longer wavelengths at lower T such that the dimensionless exponent at the peak is approximately constant (~4.97 from the transcendental x = 5(1-e^(-x)) solution). Reproduces and tightens the upstream `Equation: BlackbodyRadiation (Eq. 4.2)` test (GasChem.jl test/radiation_fundamentals_test.jl:151-165) Earth-thermal case: upstream asserts F_B_λ ≈ 3.13e7 at rtol=5e-2, this one pins the exact IEEE-754 result 31217606.963872723 at rel=1e-9.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
