                {
                    "id": "strict_positive_solar_visible_5800K_500nm",
                    "description": "First of the three strictly-positive anchor cases reproducing the upstream `Limiting: Blackbody radiation non-negative for all positive T and λ` test (GasChem.jl test/radiation_fundamentals_test.jl:305-328) which asserts F_B_λ > 0 strictly at three physically-relevant (T, λ) triples. At T=5800 K, λ=500 nm (visible-green solar peak), F_B_λ = 84565887378394.64 W/m³ — pinning a positive value enforces strict positivity by construction. Duplicates `upstream_solar_peak_5800K_500nm` to surface the regression independently if the strict-positivity series breaks while the equation-verification anchor still passes.",
