                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "F_B_λ", "time": 0.0, "expected": 12846751836.984661}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "nonneg_T100K_lam1e-7m",
                    "description": "Cold-source UV underflow case in the upstream `Limiting: Blackbody radiation non-negative` 5×4 grid (test/radiation_fundamentals_test.jl:314-320). At T=100 K, λ=100 nm the exponent c·h/(k_B·λ·T) ≈ 1438.4 ≫ 1, so exp(1438) overflows to +Inf in IEEE-754; F_B_λ = finite_numerator / (+Inf - 1) = finite / +Inf = +0.0. Upstream test comment: 'at extreme combinations (e.g., T=100K, λ=100nm), the exponent ch/kλT can exceed ~1400, causing numerical underflow to 0.0'. Asserted at abs=1e-12 (the value is exactly 0.0 by IEEE-754 division-by-infinity rule; abs tolerance gates stuck-at-nonzero regressions).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "T": 100.0,
                        "λ": 1.0e-7
                    },
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "F_B_λ", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": {"abs": 1.0e-12}}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "nonneg_T100K_lam1um",
                    "description": "Cold-source IR case in the upstream non-negativity grid. At T=100 K, λ=1 μm the exponent ch/kλT ≈ 143.84, exp(143.84) ≈ 5.65e62, so F_B_λ ≈ 2π·c²·h·λ⁻⁵ / exp(143.84) ≈ 1.27e-48 W/m³ — vanishingly small but strictly positive (no overflow). At T=100 K Wien's peak is at λ_max = 2.897e-5 m = 28.97 μm, so 1 μm is deep in the short-wavelength Wien tail where the spectrum exponentially decays. Pins the exact value at rel=1e-9.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "T": 100.0,
                        "λ": 1.0e-6
                    },
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "F_B_λ", "time": 0.0, "expected": 1.2730186220843828e-48}
                    ]
