                    "description": "Wien-peak verification at T=300 K (Earth-surface): at λ_peak = b/T = 2.897e-3/300 = 9.656666666666667e-6 m, F_B_λ = 31308528.22939951 W/m³ — the maximum-emission spectral density per Wien's displacement law. Reproduces the upstream `Analytical: Planck spectrum peak matches Wien prediction` test (GasChem.jl test/radiation_fundamentals_test.jl:423-453) which asserts F_B_λ at λ_peak > F_B_λ at 0.9·λ_peak AND > F_B_λ at 1.1·λ_peak for each of T ∈ {300, 1000, 5800} K. The strict inequality F_peak > F_0.9 and F_peak > F_1.1 is exact by IEEE-754 since the Planck-function is strictly concave at its maximum.",
